<TR>
<TD vAlign=top>This screen left&nbsp;will confirm to your that you have acepted the licensing agreement and that the installation will commence on clicking the <strong>Start install and Setup</strong> button provided.</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><HR><br /><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="25" alt="" /><br><span class="contentHead">Database Setup</span><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt=""><br /><table width="158" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" class="table_class">
<tr><td class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MV8xODhfV3ozS1RXNFU5Vy5qcGc.html" onClick="window.open('zoom/MV8xODhfV3ozS1RXNFU5Vy5qcGc.html','previewpic','width=538,height=312');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/1_188_Wz3KTW4U9W-150x.jpg" width="150" height="87" border="0" class="image_img" alt="" /></a></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td align="center" bgcolor="FCFCFC" class="image_caption"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /><br><img src="picture/icon_lupe_.gif" border="0" alt="" /><img src="content/gt/fb4f6e4639b2d7e2b19b7ea01fe84770.png" alt="Zoom" border="0" /><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
</table><div class="articleText">For this step you will need your mySQL database login details (Database name, User name &amp; User password). If you do not yet know your database login details you should ask host for this. You Will only need to use the <STRONG>prepend table names</STRONG> If you intented to install more than one version of phpWCMS within the same database. If you are unsure of this the you are advised to leave this field empty.<BR><BR>If this is your first installation of phpWMS and no previous database has been installed you should now check the <STRONG>create all tables</STRONG> instructing the setup process to build the database structure automatically. Leaving this box unchecked is for those users whom are updating or reinstalling phpWCMS over an existing version.<BR><BR>Your final task in this step is to click on the <STRONG>send db data </STRONG>any errors within this step are more than likely to be caused and cured by the validaty of data that you have provided and you should check that all is correct before continuing with this setup.<BR><BR></div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><HR><br /><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="25" alt="" /><br><span class="contentHead">Site information and Webmaster account</span><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt=""><br /><table width="158" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" class="table_class">
<tr><td class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MV8xODlfbVVBMlZlczQ1SC5qcGc.html" onClick="window.open('zoom/MV8xODlfbVVBMlZlczQ1SC5qcGc.html','previewpic','width=538,height=481');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/1_189_mUA2Ves45H-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="134" border="0" class="image_img" alt="" /></a></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td align="center" bgcolor="FCFCFC" class="image_caption"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /><br><i>fig 1.4</i> (Click to enlarge)<br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
</table><div class="articleText">Step 4 requests that you provide details of your website and for the default Webmaster/Administrator of the site <i>fig 1.4</i>.
<br />
The first field is for your full domain address followed by a 'trailing slash' <strong>/</strong>
<br />
The next three fields setup the 'User name', 'User password' and 'e-mail address' for the Webmaster/Administrator. The details you supply in this step are <strong>not</strong> equivalent to your database details from step 3. It is strongly recommended that you do not use the same information for both steps.
<br /><br />
If you had checked the <strong>Create all DB tables</strong> in the previous step the nyou <strong>must</strong> chack the <strong>create admin account</strong> in this step otherwise no admin account would be created thus providing you with no way of loging in.
<br /><br />
The remaining fields may be left 'as is' unless you fully understand the settings you wish to use here. You will be able to change and alter the settign for these fields at a later date via  edits to the include/conf.inc.php
<br />
Click the <strong>send site data</strong> button to commit the information and proceed to step 5.</div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><HR><br /><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="25" alt="" /><br><span class="contentHead">Setup Pathes Values</span><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt=""><br /><table width="158" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" class="table_class">
<tr><td class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MV8xOTRfeGpDM2N2MG5MWC5qcGc.html" onClick="window.open('zoom/MV8xOTRfeGpDM2N2MG5MWC5qcGc.html','previewpic','width=538,height=536');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/1_194_xjC3cv0nLX-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="149" border="0" class="image_img" alt="" /></a></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td align="center" bgcolor="FCFCFC" class="image_caption"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /><br><i>fig 1.5</i> (Click to enlarge)<br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
</table><div class="articleText">Normally you don't need to change here anything.
<br /><br />
Only take a look at the field "<strong>phpwcms root</strong>", wich only should filled out with the subdir where your phpWCMS is uploaded.
<br /><br />
Hit the "<strong>send path values</strong>" button to come to the next step.
<br /><br /><br /></div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="60" alt="" /><br /><HR><br /><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="25" alt="" /><br><span class="contentHead">Content Settings</span><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt=""><br /><table width="158" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" class="table_class">
<tr><td class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MV8xOTFfakFtRHRncFAwai5qcGc.html" onClick="window.open('zoom/MV8xOTFfakFtRHRncFAwai5qcGc.html','previewpic','width=538,height=458');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/1_191_jAmDtgpP0j-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="128" border="0" class="image_img" alt="" /></a></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td align="center" bgcolor="FCFCFC" class="image_caption"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /><br><i>fig 1.6</i> (Click to enlarge)<br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
</table><div class="articleText">This step (<i>fig 1.6</i>) offers a few configurable setting. It is not nessasery to alter any settigns here unless you fully understand thier implications fully.
<br /><br />
In the field&nbsp; "<strong>upload file size</strong>" you can setup the maximum file size wich will be allowed to upload. via the filecenter in the backend.
<br /><br />
"<strong>content width</strong>" determine the width of the main content area.
<br /><br />
"<strong>list image</strong>" determine the size of the preview images.
<br /><br />
"<strong>preview image</strong>" determine the size of the images in normal view.
<br /><br />
"<strong>logout time</strong>" determine after wich inactivity you ill be logged out. Standard is 1800 seconds, wich will be 30 min.
<br /><br />
"<strong>page compression</strong>" determine if the page compression will be enabled..
<br /><br />
And at last you can setup a the "<strong>charset</strong>".
<br /><br />
Hit the "<strong>send content values</strong>" button to come to the last step.</div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><HR><br /><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="25" alt="" /><br><span class="contentHead">create and upload the conf.inc.php</span><br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt=""><br /><table width="158" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" class="table_class">
<tr><td class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MV8xOTJfOEJmWmtIYklOby5qcGc.html" onClick="window.open('zoom/MV8xOTJfOEJmWmtIYklOby5qcGc.html','previewpic','width=538,height=500');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/1_192_8BfZkHbINo-150x150.jpg" width="150" height="139" border="0" class="image_img" alt="" /></a></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td></tr>
<tr><td align="center" bgcolor="FCFCFC" class="image_caption"><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /><br><i>fig 1.7</i> (Click to enlarge)<br><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="3" alt="" /></td><td><img src="img/leer.gif" width="8" height="1" alt="" /></td></tr>
</table><div class="articleText">So if everything has gone well and there are no permissions or path problems then your screen should resemble <i>fig 1.7</i>
<br /><br />
If not, you should now refer to <a href="errormessages_inst.phtml" target="_blank">Error messages</a> and correct any errors before continuing.
<br /><br />
Once you have a full compliment of green boxes you should now download and save the newly generated <strong>config.inc.php </strong>file to your <strong>include/inc_conf/conf..inc.php</strong> replacing the existing file. 
<br /><br />
<strong>Now please delete the Setup folder</strong> as this would now presents a security risk to your website. 
<br /><br />
Once completed you have successfully completed you phpWCMS instalation.
<br />
You may now<strong>LOGIN</strong> via link in the upper right of your screen to the backend with the username and password presented in step 4.</div><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div><img src="img/leer.gif" width="1" height="15" alt="" /><br /><STRONG>Next ...<BR><a href="errormessages_inst.phtml">Installation Errormessages</a></STRONG>
